<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3545270>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Euplanoida cf. pacificola. A, E-K. (UMAR-PLAT 001); B (UMAR-PLAT 002), C (UMAR-PLAT 003), D (UMAR- PLAT 004). A-D. specimens in vivo; E. specimen stained in Mayer’s carmalum and cleared in methyl salicylate; F-G. anterior region of the body; H. pharynx region; I-K. male and female reproductive system, ventral view. Structures: b= brain, ce= cerebral eyes, gcm=globuli cell masses, lv= Lang´s vesicle, ovi= oviducts, p= pharynx, pp= penis papilla, sd= spermiducal ducts, sv= seminal vesicle, spv= spermiducal vesicle, te= tentacular eyes. Scaling bar of the figure A-E = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3545270/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3545280>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Bivesiculoplana lamothei. A, D-F, H-K (UMAR-PLAT 008); G (UMAR-PLAT 009); B-C (UMAR-PLAT 011); A. specimen in vivo associate a Fissurella gemmata; B-C. Specimen preserved in alcohol associate a Lottia sp.; D. specimen stained in Mayer’s carmalum and cleared in methyl salicylate associate a F. gemmata; E-F, H. anterior region of the body; G. region subepidermal; I. pharynx; J. Lang´s vesicle, ventral view; K. male and female reproductive system, ventral view. Structures: b= brain, ce= cerebral eyes, fg= female gonopore, gcm= globuli cell masses, lv= Lang´s vesicle, m= mouth, mg= male gonopore, nt= nuchal tentacle; p= pharynx, st= stylet, spv= spermiducal vesicle, te= tentacular eyes. Scaling bar of the figure A-D = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3545280/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3545284>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Bivesiculoplana lamothei; A, E, F (UMAR-PLAT 011C-E), B–D, G–I (UMAR-PLAT 011A-B); A, E, F. male and female reproductive system, frontal view and B–D, G–I. sagittal view. Structures: cg=cement gland, fg= female gonopore, lv= Lang´s vesicle, ma= male antrum, mg= male gonopore, ovi= oviducts, p= pharynx, pp= penis papilla, pv= prostatic vesicle, sd= spermiducal ducts, st= stylet, sv= seminal vesicle, spv= spermiducal vesicle, va= vagina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3545284/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3545286>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Paraplanocera oligoglenoides sp. nov. A (paratype UMAR-PLAT 013); B (paratype UMAR-PLAT 038); C (holotype UMAR-PLAT 012).A, F. specimen in vivo; B. specimen preserved in alcohol; C. specimen stained in Mayer’s carmalum and cleared in methyl salicylate; D-E. anterior region of the body; G. pharynx; H. male and female system reproduction, ventral view. Structures: b=brain, bc= bursa copulatrix, ce= cerebral eyes, cs=cirrus sac, d=dots, dorsal color pattern, fg= female gonopore, gcm= globuli cell masses, lv= Lang´s vesicle, m= mouth, mg= male gonopore, nt= nuchal tentacle, p= pharynx, pv= prostatic vesicle, spv= spermiducal vesicle, te= tentacular eyes. Scaling bar of the figure A-C= 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3545286/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3545272>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Euplanoida cf. pacificola. A (UMAR-PLAT 004G), B-E (UMAR-PLAT 004A–F). A. male and female reproductive system, frontal view; B-E. male and female reproductive system, sagittal view. Structures: cg= cement gland, dvl=duct of Lang´s vesicle, ed= ejaculatory duct, fg= female gonopore, lv= Lang´s vesicle, ma= male antrum, mg= male gonopore; ovi= oviducts, p= pharynx, pp= penis papilla, sd= spermiducal ducts, sv= seminal vesicle, spv= spermiducal vesicle, va= vagina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3545272/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3545294>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Distribution in the Mexican Pacific of the four acotyleans flatworms species recorded in this work: Bisacculosuteri marcelae sp. nov., Bivesiculoplana lamothei, Euplanoida cf. pacificola and Paraplanocera oligoglenoides sp. nov. Closed symbols denote examined material, line symbols literature records." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3545294/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

